This class provides an implementation of AuthentorizationManager SPI provided by CM for authorize the search users against SharePoint documents.. To understand how this module fits into the Connector Manager framework refer to http://code.google.com/apis/searchappliance/documentation/connectors/110/connector_dev/cdg_authorization.html

Method Detail

authorizeDocids

public java.util.Collection<com.google.enterprise.connector.spi.AuthorizationResponse> authorizeDocids(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> docIDs,
                                                                                                       com.google.enterprise.connector.spi.AuthenticationIdentity identity)
                                                                                                throws com.google.enterprise.connector.spi.RepositoryException
Authorizes a user represented by AuthenticationIdentity against all the docIDs. All the docIDs are first converted into a format as expected by the GSBulkAuthorization web service. The web service expects the documents to be sent in the form of AuthData. An instance of AuthData contains all the document specific necessary information required for authorization. We also need to categorize all the AuthData objects according to the their web application. This is required because the authorization of documents are done per Web Application. This constraint is applied by the Web Service.

Specified by:
authorizeDocids in interface com.google.enterprise.connector.spi.AuthorizationManager
Parameters:
docIDs - Document IDs to be authorized. These document IDs had been initially constructed and sent to GSA by the connector itself. The document IDs are in the format: <Parent_List_URL>|<Original_Doc_ID> The allowed prefixes to the format are: [ALERT] represents alerts which have been sent as a SPDocument [ATTACHMENT][<Attachment_URL>] The document IDs are carefully parsed to construct the AuthData object for each document.
identity - Represents the user to be authorized.
Throws:
com.google.enterprise.connector.spi.RepositoryException
